<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eastman Kodak Co.: The Rochester, N.Y., firm's 1989 profit amounted to $529 
million, down 62% from 1988, due primarily to restructuring costs. 
</P>
<P>
Sales totaled a record $18.4 billion, up 8%. For the fourth quarter, the 
company reported a $60-million loss, contrasted with earnings of $312 million 
in the year-earlier period. Sales totaled $4.9 billion, an increase of 8% and 
another record. The photographic, chemicals and pharmaceutical concern said 
despite strong sales, earnings were also restrained by inflation, higher 
interest expenses and the unfavorable impact of exchange rate fluctuations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
