<TEXT>
<P>
"The music-making immortalized on record is inevitably a mere echo of that 
experienced by the listener seated in the concert hall. . . . Even at its very 
best, the record can produce only a skeleton, which the concert clothes in the 
flesh of social energy." -- Conductor Esa-Pekka Salonen, in the Finnish Music 
Quarterly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
