<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV RATINGS; 
</P>
<P>
PAIR OF SPECIALS BREAK INTO THE TOP 20 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE MARGULIES , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The top of the A. C. Nielsen ratings list for last week looked the same as 
usual, but a couple of specials did manage to crack the Top 20. David 
Letterman's eighth anniversary special on NBC last Thursday finished 17th among 
the week's 81 prime-time programs, attracting viewers in about 15.5 million 
homes, while the tribute to Sammy Davis Jr. on ABC Sunday night ranked 19th, 
with an audience of about 15 million homes. 
</P>
<P>
The Nielsen numbers, released Tuesday, gave NBC its 16th consecutive weekly 
win. ABC was second and CBS was third. The full list of ratings is on page 11. 
</P>
<P>
* In its first outing last week, Valerie Harper's new show narrowly beat her 
old show. "City," on CBS, drew a 13.9 rating while NBC's "The Hogan Family," in 
which Harper used to star when it was called "Valerie," garnered a 13.8. But 
this week, "The Hogan Family" got the same rating and "City" fell to a 12.1 -- 
and they both lost to the second half hour of "MacGyver" on ABC, which had a 
14.3. (Each ratings point represents 921,000 homes.) 
</P>
