<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 6 INMATES ACCEPT COUNTY OFFER IN CIVIL RIGHTS 
SUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Six black inmates who claimed they were brutalized by sheriff's deputies in 
racially motivated attacks at the Hall of Justice jail accepted an offer by the 
county Tuesday to settle a civil rights suit. 
</P>
<P>
At the county's request, attorneys would not disclose the amount of the 
settlement, reached just before trial was to begin in a case triggered by 
fracases in the Los Angeles Hall of Justice. 
</P>
<P>
One of the plaintiffs, Sammy E. Carlyle, was left wheelchair-bound as a result 
of injuries he sustained in one incident. Richard Eiden, an attorney for the 
plaintiffs, said only that the offer was adequate. 
</P>
