<P>
Bruce Coslet and Joe Bugel, veteran assistant coaches in the NFL, became head 
coaches. 
</P>
<P>
Coslet, the Cincinnati Bengals' offensive coordinator, was hired by the New 
York Jets to succeed Joe Walton. Bugel, the offensive coordinator for the 
Washington Redskins, replaces Gene Stallings and interim coach Hank Kuhlmann 
with the Phoenix Cardinals. 
</P>
<P>
Coslet, 43, takes over a Jet team that went from an 8-7-1 record in 1988 to 
4-12 last season. 
</P>
<P>
