<P>
ORANGE LUTHERAN'S PARKINSON SETS MARK WITH 6-GOAL GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Freshman forward Amber Parkinson scored a county-record six goals in Orange 
Lutheran High School's 10-0 victory over Brethren in an Olympic League girls' 
soccer match Tuesday in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
Parkinson, who has 30 goals this season, scored four in the first half and two 
in the second before leaving the game midway through the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Parkinson's six goals in a game ties her with four others for third place on 
the all-time Southern Section list. The Southern Section record for goals in a 
game is held by Shannon Maddock of Torrance, who had eight against Long Beach 
Wilson during the 1984-85 season. 
</P>
