SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
EX-MCMARTIN DEFENDANTS FILE SLANDER SUIT AGAINST PARENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three former McMartin Pre-School defendants filed a slander suit today against 
the parent of a child allegedly molested at the school, charging that he has 
defamed them in interviews on national talk shows. 
</P>
<P>
The Superior Court suit against Robert Currie was filed by the founder of the 
preschool, Virginia McMartin; her daughter, Peggy McMartin Buckey, and her 
granddaughter, Peggy Anne Buckey. 
</P>
<P>
The suit was filed in response to remarks Currie made on a number of television 
talk shows following the Jan. 18 acquittals of Peggy McMartin Buckey, 63, and 
her son, Ray Buckey, 31, on 52 molestation counts stemming from the alleged 
sexual abuse of pupils at the preschool from 1978 to '83. 
</P>
<P>
The suit claims that since the verdicts, Currie has continued to state his 
belief that all the defendants in the case are guilty. 
</P>
