</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
British rock star Billy Idol was recovering today after undergoing seven hours 
of surgery to repair a serious leg fracture suffered in a motorcycle accident, 
a hospital official said. 
</P>
<P>
Idol, 34, nursing a "major break" of his right leg and a fractured left arm 
suffered in the accident Tuesday morning, remained in serious but stable 
condition at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center, hospital spokesman Ron Wise said. 
</P>
<P>
Ellen Golden, Idol's publicist, said it is unclear how his injuries might 
affect his career. 
</P>
<P>
Idol was planning a tour to support his new album and has a role in director 
Oliver Stone's upcoming film about the 1960s rock group The Doors. The film is 
scheduled to begin shooting in three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
Wise said Idol will probably be hospitalized for at least two weeks, recovering 
from injuries that took three orthopedic surgeons seven hours to repair. 
</P>
